dal court to the modern city-state, advanced by the rising mercantile class. Working at the intersection of textual, material, and cultural elements, this study complements the current state of scholarship by providing information and answers informed by an in-depth analysis of the manuscript culture and its role in the birth and development of European vernacular traditions. Furthermore, Dante and the Dynamics of Textual Exchange expands the literature's understanding of the dynamics between a text and its material support by looking at this relationship within a broader framework of intercultural exchange, which suggests an increased dynamics and fluidity between cultures.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2021) 0aLiterature and societyzItalyxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aManuscripts, Medieval - Italy - History - To 1500. 0aManuscripts, MedievalzItalyxHistoryyTo 1500. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Medieval.2bisacsh  aAccessus ad auctores.  aDante.  aItalian Literature.  aNew Life.  aOld Occitan.  aProsimetrum.  aProvençal.  aVita Nova.  aVita Nuova.  aauthor.  aauthorship.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311072901640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780823270255zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823270255423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780823270255.jpg  a978-3-11-072901-6  Fordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK